# .rules — Portfolio Project Rules
# Antigravity reads this file to generate consistent code throughout the project.

## Tech Stack
- React 18 + Vite + Tailwind CSS
- No class components — only functional + hooks
- JS (no TypeScript for now)
- lucide-react for icons (no Github/Linkedin icons — use SVG inline instead)

## Code Style
- Component names: PascalCase (e.g. ProjectCard.jsx)
- Functions/variables: camelCase
- No inline styles — use Tailwind classes only
- Max 80 lines per component — split if bigger

## Folder Structure
- Each section = src/sections/SectionName.jsx
- Reusable UI = src/components/
- All hardcoded data = src/data/ (not in JSX)
- Custom hooks = src/hooks/
- Images/assets = src/assets/
- Helper functions = src/utils/

## Quality Rules
- No hardcoded text in JSX — put in data files
- Every component must have a JSDoc comment describing its purpose
- No console.log in production code
- Responsive design mandatory (mobile-first)
- PropTypes used where props are passed

## Naming Conventions
- Files: PascalCase for components, camelCase for utils and hooks
- CSS classes: use Tailwind only, no custom CSS unless absolutely necessary
- Images: descriptive names (profile-photo.webp not img1.jpg)

## Scalability
- New project = only update src/data/projects.js
- New skill = only update src/data/skills.js
- New experience = only update src/data/experience.js
- Sections must be independently removable/addable in App.jsx
